data.title: Triple jump: Nathan Douglas has a spring in his step after long journey back from injury

data.text:
When he steps out into the stadium at the Commonwealth Games this week, Nathan Douglas will be scanning the sea of faces in the crowd, trying to spot his mum.

“When you’re out there, it’s almost just you and this massive stadium,” says the 35-year-old triple jumper, who is competing in his third Commonwealth Games on Australia’s Gold Coast. “If you’ve got some people who you know are in the stadium, it doesn’t feel so lonely… like you’re doing it as a team, really.

“My mum will tell me where her seat is and I’ll try to look . . . they normally have a flag,” he says, smiling.
